<head>LACQUER</head><list type="translations"><item xml:lang="zh">漆</item><item xml:lang="och">漆</item></list>
<div type="definition">
<p>SUBSTANCE USED to CAUSE SURFACES TO BECOME INTENSELY SMOOTH AND TO RESEMBLE GLASS. []</p></div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current general term for lacquer is qī 漆.</p>
<p>2. Xiū 髹 refers either to the black and red lacquer, or to the lacquer in general.</p>
<p>3. Yóu qī 油漆 can also refer to the lacquer, as it contains oil.</p></div></div>
